      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALL MUCKED UP (1) is better than last start when fourth (16.57) from Box 2 at Healesville over 300m. Ready to return to form. BIG EASY AL (6) turned in a better effort at this track last start, finishing second behind Lindenow Buster (26.02) in a Grade 4/5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Can measure up. CINDY CABANG (2) was unwanted in betting last start but proved too quick with an all-the-way win over 450m at Ballarat in a Grade 5, scoring by 1.3 lengths (25.84). Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to her credit. Should feature again. KENZIE KID (7) gets a chance to improve on an unplaced run at her latest outing at this circuit.",
